			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi All:
<br />

<br />
   I don't like to compare the classes,
<br />
   but BST's pet seems unfair in my opinion.
<br />
   In another post, I saw mage's pet is only 3% better
<br />
   than BST's.
<br />

<br />
   Maybe BST is a pet class, but wait....
<br />
   BST is considered as a hybrid,
<br />
   even without pet, BST is a Monk/Shaman,
<br />
   which is good enough.
<br />

<br />
   If it's considered as a pet class,
<br />
   and only 3% worse than mage's pet,
<br />
   why BST has a better Solo and Group ability,
<br />
   better defense, while having better Pet Heals?
<br />

<br />
   And okay, if BST deserve the utility,
<br />
   remember, mage pets are specialized.
<br />
   How come specialzed pets are only 3% better
<br />
   than generalized one?
<br />

<br />
   Maybe it's just my bias,
<br />
   but in my opinion, mages pet should be a lot better.
<br />

