				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hell, all I know is this.  
<br />

<br />
When I am in group or LDoN where there is a BST present, and we end up with one more mob than tanks, the BST off-tanks it.  Not only does he send his pet to take on the mob and assumes aggro to alleviate the tank's damage, but he then turns to help the main tank and begins to whack away at the first mob while the 2nd mob is beating on his back.
<br />

<br />
Now I am not talking about taking one or two hits while the tank establishes aggro, I am talking about allowing the mob to beat on him until the primary target is dead.  If necessary, he will turn and take the 2nd mob solo.  I also happen to be referring to a level 62+ group doing a normal LDoN or a tier 2 group, so it's not like the mob is just taking small bites either.  I am also not referring to a single uber-BST that was very good at his role either, I have witnessed it with multiple different players, some of which were not even all that good at playing the class.
<br />

<br />
At no point would I ever attempt to do the same thing, it simply is not viable.  When we finish taking down the first mob, we look at the 2nd, and it is usually around 45-55% health from a single BST pet chewing on it.  In a similar scenario, my pet would be dead, and I with it.
<br />

<br />
Now I ask anyone to explain how that is fair?  I didn't mention anything aside from pets and the tankability of their masters, so it is a controlled set of variables.  For a mage supposedly being the "premiere" pet class and having so much rely on our pet's abilities, it sure seems a tad skewed to me. 
<br />

<br />
I still love the ideal of the mage, and will finish playing mine until I quit EQ because after all, it is just a damn game, and this is how I have chosen to spend my time and money.  But, I do get a little frustrated when a class that is so similar to my own can outperform me as if I was not even there.  Yeah, I toss in a few nukes when the BST can't, and the BST can slow, etc. to compensate for lack of nukes, but when all is said and done, the BST class seems to edge out the mage class when it comes to being a pet class.
<br />

<br />
I would never ask that the BST be nerfed in any way.  I for one love to have them with on groups and adventures as they are damn valuable.  I would just like to have that feeling be mutual, and as of right now it really is not.  It sucks to sit and watch another class be able to do the things that you thought you were supposed to be able to as the "pet" class of EQ.  I would just want to be upgraded a little in the lines of pet heals, pet damage and mitigation, and maybe be able to summon some per weapons that can proc a snare or slow to help everyone out a little.
<br />

<br />
Well, that's about as much bitching as I am capable of, so I leave the rest to those that are more practiced and blinded by your class biases.
<br />

<br />
Adieu<br />_________________<br />Artificial Intelligence stands no chance against Natural Stupidity.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=725127" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stasys</a>
<br />
The Nameless</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Stasys Prymordii on Wed Mar 24, 2004 7:26 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
