<br />
Ok, here we go...
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If it's considered as a pet class, 
<br />
and only 3% worse than mage's pet, 
<br />
why BST has a better Solo and Group ability, 
<br />
better defense, while having better Pet Heals? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Not sure where this 3% figure comes from, mage pet's melee DPS ranges from about even on RS(which is not a DPS pet) to 10dps greater with WoX (standard soloing pet+ damage as long as chain petting is not required) to 25dps+ using SoM depending on how well the mob is kept positioned correctly for BSing.  I'm not even going to comment on CoR because we all know sparky has issues  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="Laughing" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
If you are talking about tanking, both RS and WoX(the pets you would use to actually tank anything) but outtank the level 64 bst warder... so where is this 3% figure from?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Or they could just give us a much better pet period... </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
All mages are hoping with the upcoming pet changes being considered that this will happen.  Just looking through the forums here you will see plenty if cross-posts linked form the necro and bst forums that easily show that both of these classes realize how much mages need upgrades to their pets to make up for the lack of utility.  I'm not sure why this post has to keep popping up seeing as all pet classes seem to be in agreement here.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">There is already a sufficient reason to add a beastlord over a mage if a group is lacking slow, and mages already do superior dps in a group therefore mages and beastlords don't directly compete with one another group groups so I don't really see how the quality of our pets affects beastlords.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This comment is very true.  The biggest issue you see bsts respond on these threads is simply that bsts are constantly being compared to mages BY mages, not the other way around.  After seeing so many whines and complaints to nerf bsts, you will eventually get response from them.  Tell me exactly, how would any bst nerf directly upgrade mages?  Answer, it wouldn't.  Mages would still compain because no upgrades had been given to their pet regardless of any downgrades applied to the bst class... I think many people need to get this through their head and drop the issue already and stick to upgrading the mage class.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I think BST's pet does too many damage too. 
