<br />
both wielding the same reason.   </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">  
<br />

<br />
3 damage?  Not sure what thin air you keep pulling these facts from.  Without fucus,the level 62 warder hits for 73, and the 64 warder hits for 77.  Unfocused RS hits for 79, WoX hits for 83, and SoM hits for 81... and again, if sparky is meleeing there is something wrong.  So again, where are you getting your facts from, as not one of these pets has a difference of 3.  Also, the bst pet procs quite often because of a thing called DEXTERITY.  Yes, as a shaman hybrid we recieve dexterity buffs we can cast on others and our pet alike.  Cast those same buffs on any of the mage pets and you will see a drastic increase in procs from weapons given.  This is a non issue.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">When I am in group or LDoN where there is a BST present, and we end up with one more mob than tanks, the BST off-tanks it. Not only does he send his pet to take on the mob and assumes aggro to alleviate the tank's damage, but he then turns to help the main tank and begins to whack away at the first mob while the 2nd mob is beating on his back. 
<br />

<br />
Now I am not talking about taking one or two hits while the tank establishes aggro, I am talking about allowing the mob to beat on him until the primary target is dead. If necessary, he will turn and take the 2nd mob solo. I also happen to be referring to a level 62+ group doing a normal LDoN or a tier 2 group, so it's not like the mob is just taking small bites either. I am also not referring to a single uber-BST that was very good at his role either, I have witnessed it with multiple different players, some of which were not even all that good at playing the class. 
<br />

<br />
At no point would I ever attempt to do the same thing, it simply is not viable. When we finish taking down the first mob, we look at the 2nd, and it is usually around 45-55% health from a single BST pet chewing on it. In a similar scenario, my pet would be dead, and I with it. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
 
<br />
Umm, that's because bsts are a melee class, not a priest or caster, and therefor are meant to take a few hits.  Yes, slow is a powerful tool, but you will notice most times that if a bst is invited, it's because of the fact that the group needs a slower, not because our pets are vastly superior to a mage's.   I assure you that if you were to have the mage pet offtank the same slowed mob, not only would it live but the mob would have less life left by the time the group turned it's attention to it, as mage pets put out better dps.  It has nothing to do with the bst pet being better, as it is not.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Have any of you guys seen that episode of Futurama where Fry spends his $300 tax refund on 100 cups of coffee? 
