</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Secondly, I spend all the time I can afford this game either playing EQ or perusing the boards for my own class. It must take a hell of an effort to have posted 122 times on the boards of another class, and you must be awfully interested in what we have going on to dedicate the time wading through the posts here to monitor what we have going on. I can imagine posting a couple times, or a dozen on issues that are of particular interest, but to have tacked 120+ items into discussion here is a hell of a lot if you are not a mage. Have you played a mage, does what we discuss here really warrant that much attention to the point that other classes feel the need to come in and tell us that we are wrong or is this just the sad state that public forums have become? 
